text:
Multiplication is actually much simpler than what Gura described, it was just explained to her in a way that helped her to learn. It took me till I was 32 about 7 or 8 months ago when I learned how easy and insanely fast it actually is without even thinking about it.

Say 9x9. When you're multiplying, all you actually have to do is learn and know what the basic addition of 9+9 is which is 18, this is where you connect to how easy quick and insanely fast this is. So do 9+9, then add another 9 which is 27, add another 9 and it's 36. If you don't see the pattern look at the final digit in the Ones place in the sequence of pattern (8 is in the Ones place in the sequence pattern of 18, 7 is in the Ones place in the second sequence of pattern, and 6 is in the Ones place in the third sequence of the pattern). The pattern you should notice is that it's counting down by 1 from your first number (9) which arguably makes 9 the first number in the pattern sequence but in general terms of explaining I wanted you to notice the pattern of how its counting down and why this connects to being able to do multiplication really fast without having to think about it.

9x9 is 81, which is obvious for anyone who should already know immediately that 9x10 is 90. Pattern sequence for multiples of 9 are (9, 18, 27, 36, 45, 54, 63, 72, 81, 90, 99, 108, 117, 126, 135, 144, 153, 162, 171, 180, 189) and so on.

If you were to do multiples of 8, pattern sequence counts down by 2, multiples of 7 counts down by 3, and so on and so forth.

Here's some examples (in as short form as I can put them to not make everyone tune out) from streams of late why I said what I did: Gura saying her Atlantis project has her so intimidated that she has been hesitant to boot the game up. Gura saying it "must've been painful for you to watch" about her "only built a door" stream, because she said she also watched the clips and "If it was painful for you to watch, it was painful for me too". She said "What stings about it the most is that it was the stream where I had the to-do list up, I was going to do the list, it was going to be perfect, it was going to be there the whole time" (referring to not getting distracted as chat had berated her for it before) "...and then I did nothing on that list.... (long pause) and that was the stream."

That was all after a comment about "will you make a door" that got a fake giggle and a sigh. I guarantee you she felt bad about that stream.

In the same stream she said she feels "bad for not having contributed enough on the EN server" and that she wants to change it, talked about wanting to change laziness, said she's not surprised Ame likes to work alone as Gura can be "dead weight" etc.

In this stream she said she thought she might be getting sick but the only symptom is shortness of breath, which for me is always a symptom of anxiety.

I'm well aware that barely anyone on the chat side is taking any of it seriously and seem to think she's trolling when she's panicing to the point of flipflopping hopelessly between projects seemingly hoping to manage to do something chat doesn't vocally describe as "hurting their brain", but it seems to me she might be a little more sensitive than people think about such things. Banter's fine though. Ame and her chat have banter.. and she strikes back. But 30 minutes of mockery about the same thing in a row and laughing about it in Ina's, Haachama's, Ame's chat the following days in the form of chat spam isn't my idea of "banter".

She isn't new to this, I know... but she sure as hell is new to being watched by half a million people almost daily. She never did anything close to that before these few months.
